{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019XK5WeNiSbR3muunoi5YYw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information you requested. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary of Database Patterns in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n### 1. `getPlayerStats` Method Implementation\n\n**Location:** Lines 1147-1179\n\nThe method computes aggregate statistics from the `transactions` table using SQL aggregation:\n\n```typescript\nasync getPlayerStats(wallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<\n    Array<{\n      games_played: string;\n      total_wagered: string;\n      total_wins: string;\n      net_pnl: string;\n    }>\n  >`\n    SELECT\n      COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN tx_type = 'deposit' THEN match_id END)::text AS games_played,\n      COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN tx_type = 'deposit' THEN amount_lamports ELSE 0 END), 0)::text AS total_wagered,\n      COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN tx_type = 'payout' THEN match_id END)::text AS total_wins,\n      COALESCE(\n        SUM(CASE WHEN tx_type IN ('payout', 'refund') THEN amount_lamports\n                 WHEN tx_type = 'deposit' THEN -amount_lamports\n                 ELSE 0 END),\n        0\n      )::text AS net_pnl\n    FROM transactions\n    WHERE wallet = ${wallet}\n  `;\n  const row = rows[0]!;\n  const gamesPlayed = Number(row.games_played);\n  const totalWins = Number(row.total_wins);\n  return {\n    gamesPlayed,\n    totalWagered: BigInt(row.total_wagered),\n    totalWins,\n    winRate: gamesPlayed > 0 ? totalWins / gamesPlayed : 0,\n    netPnl: BigInt(row.net_pnl),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Return Type:** `PlayerStats` (see type definition below)\n\n### 2. `Db` Interface - All Method Signatures\n\n**Location:** Lines 243-497\n\nThe interface defines 40+ methods organized into sections:\n\n**Rounds:**\n- `insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>`\n- `deleteRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<boolean>`\n- `updateRoundPhase(...): Promise<Round>`\n- `updateRoundEntries(...): Promise<Round>`\n- `getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>`\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase: RoundPhase): Promise<Round[]>`\n- `getRoundByMatchId(matchId: string): Promise<Round | undefined>`\n- `getRecentSettledRounds(game: string, limit: number): Promise<Round[]>`\n- `getUnsettledStats(): Promise<{ count: number; oldestAgeSeconds: number }>`\n\n**Operator Events:**\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda: string | null, eventType: OperatorEventType, payload?: unknown): Promise<OperatorEvent>`\n- `getLatestOperatorEvent(pda: string, eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<OperatorEvent | undefined>`\n- `getLatestOperatorEventsForPdas(pdas: string[], eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<Map<string, OperatorEvent>>`\n\n**Close Call Rounds:**\n- `insertCloseCallRound(params: InsertCloseCallRoundParams): Promise<CloseCallRound>`\n- `getCloseCallRound(roundId: string): Promise<CloseCallRound | undefined>`\n- `getCloseCallCurrentRound(): Promise<CloseCallRound | undefined>`\n- `getCloseCallHistory(limit: number): Promise<CloseCallRound[]>`\n- `settleCloseCallRound(roundId: string, updates: {...}): Promise<CloseCallRound>`\n\n**Transactions:**\n- `insertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>`\n- `insertTransactions(params: InsertTransactionParams[]): Promise<void>`\n- `getTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<Transaction[]>`\n\n**Referral - Codes:**\n- `insertReferralCode(wallet: string, code: string): Promise<ReferralCode>`\n- `getReferralCodeByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<ReferralCode | undefined>`\n- `getReferralCodeByCode(code: string): Promise<ReferralCode | undefined>`\n\n**Referral - Links:**\n- `insertReferralLink(referrerWallet: string, refereeWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink>`\n- `getReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink | undefined>`\n- `getReferralLinksByReferrer(referrerWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink[]>`\n\n**Referral - Earnings & Stats:**\n- `insertReferralEarning(params: {...}): Promise<ReferralEarning>`\n- `getPendingBalance(wallet: string): Promise<string>`\n- `getReferralEarnings(wallet: string, page: number, limit: number): Promise<{ items: ReferralEarning[]; totalPages: number }>`\n- `getReferralStats(wallet: string): Promise<ReferralStats>`\n\n**Referral - Claims & Rates:**\n- `insertReferralClaim(wallet: string, amountLamports: string): Promise<ReferralClaim>`\n- `getReferralClaim(claimId: string): Promise<ReferralClaim | undefined>`\n- `updateClaimStatus(claimId: string, status: ReferralClaim[\"status\"], meta?: {...}): Promise<ReferralClaim>`\n- `getReferrerRate(wallet: string, defaultRateBps: number): Promise<number>`\n\n**Player Profiles:**\n- `createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>`\n- `getProfileByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>`\n- `getProfileByIdentifier(identifier: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>`\n- `updateUsername(wallet: string, newUsername: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>`\n- `getPlayerStats(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerStats>` ← Query stats method\n- `getPublicPlayerStats(wallet: string): Promise<PublicPlayerStats>` ← Public-safe subset\n- `getWinStreaks(wallet: string): Promise<WinStreaks>`\n\n**Transaction Control:**\n- `withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>`\n- `close(): Promise<void>`\n\n### 3. Game Name Mapping Constants\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`, lines 140-149\n\n```typescript\nexport const GAME_IDS = {\n  COINFLIP: \"coinflip\",\n  LORD_OF_RNGS: \"lord-of-rngs\",\n  CRASH: \"crash\",\n  CLOSE_CALL: \"close-call\",\n  SLOTS: \"slots\",\n  GAME_OF_TRADES: \"game-of-trades\",\n  TUG_OF_EARN: \"tug-of-earn\",\n  CHART_COURSE: \"chart-course\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type GameId = (typeof GAME_IDS)[keyof typeof GAME_IDS];\n```\n\nThese are the canonical game identifiers used across the backend. The `game` column in the `transactions` and `rounds` tables stores these exact string values.\n\n### 4. Type Definitions\n\n**PlayerStats** (Lines 198-204):\n```typescript\nexport interface PlayerStats {\n  gamesPlayed: number;\n  totalWagered: bigint;\n  totalWins: number;\n  winRate: number;\n  netPnl: bigint;\n}\n```\n\n**PublicPlayerStats** (Lines 206-210):\n```typescript\nexport interface PublicPlayerStats {\n  gamesPlayed: number;\n  totalWins: number;\n  winRate: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Key distinction:** `PublicPlayerStats` omits `totalWagered` and `netPnl` for public display (no sensitive financial data).\n\nThere are no explicit DB name → frontend name mappings in db.ts. The game identifiers (`coinflip`, `lord-of-rngs`, `close-call`, etc.) are used as-is throughout the database layer, and the same constants are exported from the game-engine types package for consistent usage across the backend."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b73714c7-2f31-4e13-b447-25e2a49ac6c6","uuid":"ab72a903-bae7-4f7a-8730-739a53d08327","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:09:15.037Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing stats query patterns in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`. Specifically:\n1. Find the `getPlayerStats` method - show me its full implementation (SQL query, return type)\n2. Find the `Db` interface - show me all the method signatures defined on it\n3. Find any game name mapping constants (like DB name → frontend name mapping)\n4. Find the `PlayerStats` and `PublicPlayerStats` type definitions\n\nBe thorough - show me the actual code with line numbers.","agentId":"a46015c46e78e5413","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information you requested. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary of Database Patterns in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n### 1. `getPlayerStats` Method Implementation\n\n**Location:** Lines 1147-11