t: string, amountLamports: string): Promise<ReferralClaim>`\n- `getReferralClaim(claimId: string): Promise<ReferralClaim | undefined>`\n- `updateClaimStatus(claimId: string, status: ReferralClaim[\"status\"], meta?: {...}): Promise<ReferralClaim>`\n- `getReferrerRate(wallet: string, defaultRateBps: number): Promise<number>`\n\n**Player Profiles:**\n- `createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>`\n- `getProfileByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>`\n- `getProfileByIdentifier(identifier: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>`\n- `updateUsername(wallet: string, newUsername: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>`\n- `getPlayerStats(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerStats>` ← Query stats method\n- `getPublicPlayerStats(wallet: string): Promise<PublicPlayerStats>` ← Public-safe subset\n- `getWinStreaks(wallet: string): Promise<WinStreaks>`\n\n**Transaction Control:**\n- `withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>`\n- `close(): Promise<void>`\n\n### 3. Game Name Mapping Constants\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`, lines 140-149\n\n```typescript\nexport const GAME_IDS = {\n  COINFLIP: \"coinflip\",\n  LORD_OF_RNGS: \"lord-of-rngs\",\n  CRASH: \"crash\",\n  CLOSE_CALL: \"close-call\",\n  SLOTS: \"slots\",\n  GAME_OF_TRADES: \"game-of-trades\",\n  TUG_OF_EARN: \"tug-of-earn\",\n  CHART_COURSE: \"chart-course\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type GameId = (typeof GAME_IDS)[keyof typeof GAME_IDS];\n```\n\nThese are the canonical game identifiers used across the backend. The `game` column in the `transactions` and `rounds` tables stores these exact string values.\n\n### 4. Type Definitions\n\n**PlayerStats** (Lines 198-204):\n```typescript\nexport interface PlayerStats {\n  gamesPlayed: number;\n  totalWagered: bigint;\n  totalWins: number;\n  winRate: number;\n  netPnl: bigint;\n}\n```\n\n**PublicPlayerStats** (Lines 206-210):\n```typescript\nexport interface PublicPlayerStats {\n  gamesPlayed: